# Shared form (container + static) — .env.example
# Source of truth: the real `.env` set in Hedgeinform/zhenka — captured by NAME
# only (architectural principle: secrets never live in source). This file lists
# key NAMES with placeholder values; it is committed to the repo as the env
# contract. Real values are NEVER here.
#
# Value source: GitHub repo secrets. ops emits the matching `gh secret set`
# command list; the operator sets the values. At deploy time:
#   - container form: configure-env.yml upserts these onto the server .env.prod.
#   - static form:    deploy-web-*.yml bakes the VITE_* subset into the build.
#
# Filled per-project: replace the placeholder NAMES below with the project's real
# key names; keep the values as <placeholders>, never real secrets.

# --- Container runtime keys (server-side .env) ---
RUNTIME_KEY_A=<set-in-gh-secrets>
RUNTIME_KEY_B=<set-in-gh-secrets>

# --- Build-time keys (static / Vite SPA — baked into the build) ---
# Public by nature (shipped in the bundle) but still sourced from GH secrets so
# the value is not committed. Prefix VITE_ is required for Vite to expose them.
VITE_API_URL=<set-in-gh-secrets>
VITE_PUBLIC_KEY=<set-in-gh-secrets>

# --- Optional observability (only if Vector logs are wired) ---
# AXIOM_API_KEY=<set-in-gh-secrets>
# AXIOM_DATASET=<set-in-gh-secrets>
